OVERVIEW
════════

sitelen Konpute is bitmap data for a toki pona small pixel font. It covers
different visual styles of printable ASCII/Latin script, sitelen pona script,
semigraphic characters, and more.

Every glyph fits in a 8x8 block (often being of size 7x7 so as to leave blank
space between characters) and is assigned a codepoint mapped:
- to a Unicode equivalent (when possible)
- or otherwise mapped in Unicode Private Use Area, in a way which includes and
  extends how Sitelen Pona is encoded in the Under-ConScript Unicode Registry
  (UCSUR), see: https://www.kreativekorp.com/ucsur/charts/sitelen.html

Using the data (and scripts provided), it is possible to create severy type of
pixel fonts. A popular application is to create a "pixel" TTF font using the
online BitFontMaker2 tool: https://www.pentacom.jp/pentacom/bitfontmaker2/


PROJECT BACKGROUND
══════════════════

Why?
🭷🭷🭷🭷
- I like Toki Pona and I like pixel fonts and old-school aesthetics.
- tenpo kama la, mi wile pali e ilo nanpa pi toki pona.
  nimi ona li "ilo Konpute" li kepeken sitelen lili ni.


Toki Pona? Sitelen Pona? What's that?
🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷
Toki Pona is a constructed language of 120-ish core words created by Canadian
linguist Sonja Lang in 2001 to simplify thoughts and communication. Toki Pona is
simple to learn and has many applications as a philosophical, personal, and
creative language. It's also a popular conlang used on the Internet, and is a
fun and easy way to become multilingual. ISO 639-3 code for toki pona is TOK.
For more information:
 - see: https://tokipona.org
 - in toki pona, I'm jan Polijan, and here's some of my stuff:
   YouTube videos => https://www.youtube.com/c/janPolijan
   Mastodon       => https://toki.social/@janPolijan

toki pona can be written in many different ways. The two most popular are:
- the Latin alphabet (a convenient way for every electronic devices)
- Sitelen Pona, a logographic writing system invented for Toki Pona,
  and which feels like a more "native" and playful way to write the language.


SITELEN
═══════

sitelen Konpute li sona e sitelen mute ni:


sitelen Lasina
🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷

IJO Lasina_* │ SEME / KIPISI TAN NASIN UNIKO ("Unicode")
─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
pona         │ printable ASCII mapped in the "Basic Latin" block
             │ the digits are in a sitelen pona pu-style.
             │ The Latin digits are also available 
             │ in private area and can be used.
─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
wawa         │ (TODO:NOT YET, currently the basic ASCII is bold text)
             │ bold version of ASCII, this is mapped to the "Mathematical
             │ Alphanumeric Symbols" block (and in private area for the sitelen
             │ pona like numbers?)
─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
poka         │ (TODO) an italic version of ASCII, mapped to the "Mathematical
             │ Alphanumeric Symbols" and "Letterlike symbols" blocks and in
             │private area for the sitelen pona-like numbers?)
─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
linja-tu     │ a "double struck" version of ASCII, mapped to the
             │ "Mathematical Alphanumeric Symbols" and "Letterlike Symbols"
─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
lili         │ small ASCII letters. can serve as superscript. The glyphs mostly
             │ are 5x3? It is mapped to many characters in Unicode and to a few
             │ private ones
─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
lili-wawa    │ bold version of the small ASCII (TODO)
─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
namako       │ mostly characters from the "Latin-1 Supplement" block
─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
poki         │ enclosed uppercase letters. they come in 4 flavours:
             │ - enclosure can be either a square or a circle
             │ - they can be in normal or inverse enclosure
             │ those are mapped to "Enclosed Alphanumeric" and "Enclosed
             │ Alphanumeric Supplement" blocks


sitelen sama sitelen pona
🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷
sitelen pona, sitelen pona-like, UCSUR-like characters ...
those are mostly mapped to private areas.

IJO          │ NANPA    │ SEME
─────────────┼──────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
UCSUR        │ U+F19xx  │ "Sitelen Pona" block from UCSUR
wawa         │ U+F....  │ bold version of sitelen pona
lili         │ U+F....  │ sitelen pona lili (7x5) lon sewi
lili-wawa    │ U+F....  │ sitelen pona lili (7x5) pi linja wawa lon sewi
Lasina       │ U+F....  │ nimi Lasina lon nasin sama pi sitelen pona UCSUR
ante         │ U+F....  │ alternative glyphs for sitelen pona UCSUR
poka-ante    │ U+F....  │ mirror or flips of sitelen pona glyphs
nimi-tu      │ U+F....  │ pre-formed sitelen pona compound names
namako       │ U+F....  │ additional glyphs and glyphs for non-UCSUR words


sitelen pi musi supa
🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷
sitelen ni li tawa musi:

IJO          │ KIPISI TAN NASIN UNIKO ("Unicode")
─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
lipu         │ sitelen tan kipisi "Playing Cards"
Tomino       │ sitelen ale tan kipisi "Domino Tiles"
utala-lawa   │ "tokiponized" chess pieces from the "Miscellaneous Symbols" block
ante         │ glyphs for other games: Dice, Checkers, ...

sitelen
🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷🭷
mostly semigraphics characters
AS sitelen Konpute is monospaced, usage of those can give nice visuals.

IJO         │ SEME / KIPISI TAN NASIN UNIKO ("Unicode")
────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
poki        │ sitelen ale  tan kipisi "BoxDrawing"
leko        │ sitelen ale  tan kipisi "BlockElements"
leko-namako │ sitelen mute tan kipisi "Symbols For Legacy Computing"

